<text xml:lang="ta">
  <body>
    <div rend="parallel">
      <p xml:id="PN360-intro">tiṇaiyum tuṟaiyum avai (pi, ituvumatu) tantumāṟaṉaic caṅkavaruṇareṉṉum nākariyar pāṭiyatu.
      </p>
      <p xml:lang="en">  
      </p>
    </div> 
    <div rend="parallel">
      <lg xml:id="PN360">
<l>peritārāc ciṟuciṉattar</l>
<l>cilacollāṟ palakēḷviyar</l>
<l>nuṇṇuṇarviṉāṟ peruṅkoṭaiyar</l>
<l>kaluḻnaṉaiyāṟ ṟaṇṭēṟalar</l>
<l>kaṉikuyyāṟ koḻuntuvaiyar</l>
<l>tāḻuvantu taḻūumoḻiyar</l>
<l>payaṉuṟuppap palarkkāṟṟi</l>
<l>yēma māka vinnila māṇṭōr</l>
<l>cilarē peruma kēḷiṉi nāḷum</l>
<l>palarē takaiyaḵ taṟiyā tōrē</l>
<l>yaṉṉōr celvamu maṉṉi nillā</l>
<l>tiṉṉu maṟṟataṉ paṇpē yataṉāl</l>
<l>niccamu moḻukka muṭṭilai paricil</l>
<l>naccuvar kaiyi ṉirappa lōmpumati</l>
<l>yaccuvarap</l>
<l>pāṟiṟai koṇṭa paṟantalai mākata</l>
<l>kaḷḷi pōkiya kaḷari maruṅkiṉ</l>
<l>veḷḷi ṉiṟutta piṉṟaik kaḷḷoṭu</l>
<l>pullakat tiṭṭa cillaviḻ valci</l>
<l>pulaiya ṉēvap puṉmē lamarntuṇ</l>
<l>ṭaḻalvāyp pukka piṉṉum</l>
<l>palarvāyt tirāar paruttuṇ ṭōrē.</l>
</lg>
<lg xml:lang="en">
<l corresp="1">Those with little anger that is not fully satiated, </l>
<l corresp="2">those who listen to many [words] by means of few words, </l>
<l corresp="3">those with great gifts through subtle understanding, </l>
<l corresp="4">those with cool toddy [spiced] with turbid buds, </l>
<l corresp="5">those with fat meat with fruity seasoning, </l>
<l corresp="6">those with words that embrace, rejoicing at bowing down, </l>
<l corresp="7">appeasing to many people to make them have the yield, </l>
<l corresp="8">those who rule this ground so that it is protected </l>
<l corresp="9">are but few, great man – now listen: daily </l>
<l corresp="10">there are many who do now know that that is befitting, </l>
<l corresp="11">and the riches of suchlike, having lasted, are not permanent. </l>
<l corresp="12">Even now [that] is the nature of that. Therefore, </l>
<l corresp="13a-c">You are no hindrance to the daily conduct. </l>
<l corresp="13d-14">Beware of filling the hands of those who covet gifts. </l>
<l corresp="15">When fear comes, </l>
<l corresp="16">o minstrel in the waste land where the kites took a seat, </l>
<l corresp="17">in the saline soil where the spurge has gone large, </l>
<l>after they have been placed on the bier, for food </l>
<l>a little rice that is placed in the grass, along with toddy, (18f.)</l>
<l>and after, when the Pulaiyaṉ gives the command, they remained</l>
<l>on the grass [and] entered the mouth of the fire, being eaten, (20f.)</l>
<l corresp="22">they don’t remain, being superior(?) to many, those eaten by kites. </l>
</lg>
